article.description: — Jawaun Newton had 19 points to lead five Evansville players in double figures as the Purple Aces edged past Eastern Illinois 68-65 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Newton, Kuhlman carry Evansville over Eastern Illinois 68-65
article.linkText: Newton, Kuhlman carry Evansville over Eastern Illinois 68-65
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. -- — Jawaun Newton had 19 points to lead five Evansville players in double figures as the Purple Aces edged past Eastern Illinois 68-65 on Wednesday night. Evan Kuhlman added 15 points and Shamar Givance, Noah Frederking and Jax Levitch each had 11 for Evansville (1-3). Newton shot 11 for 13 from the line. Marvin Johnson had 17 points for the Panthers (2-4). Josiah Wallace added 17 points.
